        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 12 at 3:04PM CDT by NWS Huntsville AL</headline>
        <description>At 304 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles south of Leighton, or 13 miles east of Russellville, moving
northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Town Creek, Leighton, Courtland, North Courtland, Hatton, Ford City,
Red Bank, La Grange, Ne Smith, and Whiteoak.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
